  "title": "Mandibular nerve",
  "body_html": "<div>The mandibular nerve (V3) is the largest branch of the trigeminal nerve. It has 4 terminal branches. 3 of these are cutaneous branches (c):<br /><ul><li>Buccal nerve (c)</li><li>Inferior alveolar nerve (c)</li><li>Auriculotemporal nerve (c)</li><li>Lingual nerve</li></ul><br /><b>NOTE</b> for the exam you are expected to know the cutaneous branches<br /><br /><i>Image showing anatomy of mandibular nerve</i><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb401b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb401.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb401b.jpg'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div><br /><i>Image showing sensory areas supplied by mandibular nerve (seen in pink)</i><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb415b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb415.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb415b.jpg'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">2</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Anatomy</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Head & neck</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\nThe mandibular nerve (V3) is the largest branch of the trigeminal nerve. It has 4 terminal branches. 3 of these are cutaneous branches (c):<br /><ul><li>Buccal nerve (c)</li><li>Inferior alveolar nerve (c)</li><li>Auriculotemporal nerve (c)</li><li>Lingual nerve</li></ul><br /><b>NOTE</b> for the exam you are expected to know the cutaneous branches<br /><br /><i>Image showing anatomy of mandibular nerve</i><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb401b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb401.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb401b.jpg'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div><br /><i>Image showing sensory areas supplied by mandibular nerve (seen in pink)</i><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb415b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/imag